fields.description: The field is in a Corn silage/Corn silage/Alfalfa/Alfalfa/Alfalfa rotation

crops.name: 2nd year Alfalfa
crops.programDescription: The field was seeded to alfalfa in 2019 with an oat nurse crop. Oats and alfalfa were harvested for hay twice in the seeding year and 4 times in 2020.

narrative.baseline_conditions:
Cropping system: corn/corn 2018/2017
Field Notes: Center pivot irrigation
Nutrient Application: 5 tons/acre of dairy sold manure applied by broadcasting then incorporated with chisel plow in the fall of 2018. 
Notes for 2019: Alfalfa was seeded in 2019 with small grain of oats. Oats was used for feed and as a nurse crop for the alfalfa.

fields.description: This field is in a Corn/Corn/Corn/Small Grain underseeded with alfalfa/Alfalfa 3 years crop rotation. The corn is typically harvested for silage. Reduced till and no till along with some cover cropping are practiced. Manure from the 250 cow dairy is utilized for fertilizer.

narrative.baseline_conditions: Cropping system: corn/corn/corn, 2018/2017/2016\nNotes for 2019: Alfalfa was seeded in 2019 with a small grain of barley. Barley was used for feed and as a nurse crop for the alfalfa. \nNutrient Application: 8,000 gallons/acre of dairy manure sweep injected in the fall of 2018.

fields.description: Rolling hills, sandy and rocky over all.

narrative.baseline_conditions: Up until a couple years ago this site had been ripped or chisel plowed in the fall after harvest, and then field cultivated at least once in the spring before planting.  I am starting to switch from ripper, chisel plow, and field cultivator to vertical tillage, no till, and strip till.  Adding in cover crops as well.

fields.description: This field is in a Corn/Corn/Soybean/Small Grain underseeded with alfalfa/Alfalfa crop rotation. One half of the corn acres are typically harvested for silage. Reduced tillage is practiced and manure from the 60 cow dairy is utilized for fertilizer.

crops.name: Alfalfa
crops.programDescription: Alfalfa in second year of production

narrative.baseline_conditions: Cropping system: corn/corn 2018/2017\nNotes for 2019: Alfalfa was seeded in 2019 with a small grain of barley. Barley was used for feed and as a nurse crop for the alfalfa.\nNutrient Application: 8,000 gallons/acre of dairy manure sweep injected in the fall of 2017. 150 lbs/acre of potash applied and incorporated with field cultivator in the spring of 2019 before seeding.

Current crop rotation is continuous corn for grain over the past three years. Pen pack beef manure has been applied to the operation historically. The producer going forward would like to implement nutrient management planning and cover crops.
